      <head>Radio Verkehrs Aktiengesellschaft (RAVAG)</head>
      <div>
        <p>Public radio company established in February 1924. It was a joint venture of the Austrian
          federal government, the City of Vienna, and several banks. Its radio transmissions began
          on October 1, 1924, and featured classical music, literature, and lectures. From 1925 it
          began live broadcasts from opera houses and concert halls; live sports broadcasts began in
          1928. The company was dissolved soon after the Anschlu√ü in March 1938.</p>
